column2: # Check spelling in species and treatment but also generate a summary table
data2 <- data1 %>% group_by(species, treatment) %>% summarise(mean_activity = mean(activity),  standerr_activity = std.error(activity), mean_sl = mean(sl),  standerr_sl = std.error(sl),)
`summarise()` has grouped output by 'species'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
